<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-30T16:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-30T16:48:00-05:00" n="1176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1176">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/3895</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consular Agent <persName type="from">Sawday</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consular Agency</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ensenada</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-30T14:00:00-07:48">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s January 21, 6 p.m. Shipments should be confined to immediate
                            requirement of known mining operations and public works.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sawday</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>